{"name": "simple-blast", "metadata": {"name": "simple-blast", "version": "0.1.4", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pandas", "dateparser"], "summary": "A simple library for executing BLAST searches with ncbi-blast+", "upload_time": 1733900827}, "documentation": ["# simple_blast\n\nThis is a library that provides a very basic wrapper around ncbi-blast+.\nCurrently, the library supports searches with `blastn` only, but I may expand\nthe library to include wrappers for other BLAST executables if I need them.\n\n## Requirements\n\nThis library depends on Pandas for parsing BLAST output. The library has been\ntested with Pandas 1.5.3, but it likely works with other versions.\n\nOf course, this library assumes that ncbi-blast+ is installed. The library has\nbeen tested with ncbi-blast 2.12.0+, and it likely works with newer versions of\nthe software as well.\n\n## Basic usage\n\nYou can define a `blastn` search to be carried out using the `BlastnSearch`\nclass. `BlastnSearch`objects are constructed with two required\narguments&mdash;the subject sequence and the query sequence files, in that\norder. For example, to set up a `balstn` search for sequences in `seqs1.fasta`\nagainst those in `seqs2.fasta`, you could construct a `BlastnSearch` object like\nthis:\n\n```python\nfrom simple_blast import BlastnSearch\n\nsearch = BlastnSearch(\"seqs2.fasta\", \"seqs1.fasta\")\n```\n\nThe BLAST search is not carried out until you ask for the results by accessing\nthe `hits` property of the search. This property returns a Pandas dataframe\ncontaining the HSPs identified in the BLAST search.\n\n```python\nresults = search.hits\n```\n\nThe columns in the output may be configured by passing either the `out_columns`\nor `additional_columns` arguments when constructing the `BlastnSearch`. The\nformer argument overrides the set of output columns; the latter argument is\nadded to the list of default output columns.\n\nYou can also specify an e-value cutoff through the `evalue` argument.\n\n## DB caches\n\nWhen the same sequence file is used as a subject in multiple searches, it can be\nefficient to build a BLAST database up front. The `BlastDBCache` class can be\nused to handle this mostly automatically. To make a `BlastDBCache`, you need\nto specify the location of the on the file system.\n\n```python\nfrom simple_blast import BlastDBCache\n\ncache = BlastDBCache(\"cache_dir\")\n```\n\nTo add a file to the cache, use the `makedb` method.\n\n```python\ncache.makedb(\"seqs2.fasta\")\n```\n\nWhen constructing a `BlastnSearch` object, give it the `BlastDBCache` as the\n`db_cache` parameter to make the `BlastnSearch` object use the cache for\nsearches.\n\n```python\nsearch = BlastnSearch(\"seqs2.fasta\", \"seqs1.fasta\", db_cache=cache)\n```\n\nNow `search` will use the database we created for `seqs2.fasta`.\n\n<!-- This is a comment. -->\n"], "modules": [{"name": "simple_blast", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "simple_blast.BlastDBCache", "xref": {"fqname": "simple_blast.blastdb_cache.BlastDBCache", "project": null}}, {"name": "simple_blast.BlastnSearch", "xref": {"fqname": "simple_blast.blasting.BlastnSearch", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "simple_blast.blastdb", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "simple_blast.blastdb.read_nin_metadata", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "nin", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "simple_blast.blastdb.BlastDBMetadata", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "simple_blast.blastdb.BlastDBMetadata.format_version", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "simple_blast.blastdb.BlastDBMetadata.db_seqtype", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["protein (\"p\") or nucleic acid (\"n\")"]}, {"name": "simple_blast.blastdb.BlastDBMetadata.title", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "simple_blast.blastdb.BlastDBMetadata.date", "type": {"name": "datetime.datetime", "xref": {"fqname": "datetime.datetime", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "simple_blast.blastdb.BlastDBMetadata.num_oids", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "simple_blast.blastdb.BlastDBMetadata.vol_len", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "simple_blast.blastdb.BlastDBMetadata.max_len", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "simple_blast.blastdb.BlastDBMetadata.volume", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "simple_blast.blastdb.BlastDBMetadata.lmdb_file", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "simple_blast.blastdb.UnsupportedDatabaseFormatException", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "simple_blast.blasting", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "simple_blast.blasting.default_out_columns", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "simple_blast.blasting.yes_no", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "simple_blast.blasting.NotInDatabaseError", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "simple_blast.blasting.BlastnSearch", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "simple_blast.blasting.BlastnSearch.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "subject", "type": {"name": "str | Path | Iterable[str] | Iterable[Path]", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "query", "type": {"name": "str | Path", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "evalue", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "out_columns", "type": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "additional_columns", "type": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "db_cache", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "BlastDBCache", "xref": {"fqname": "simple_blast.blasting.blastdb_cache.BlastDBCache", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "threads", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "dust", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "task", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "max_targets", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "n_seqidlist", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "debug", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Construct a BlastnSearch with the specified settings.\n\nThis constructor requires paths to FASTA files containing the query and\nsubject sequences to use in the search.\n\nOptionally, the caller may provide an expect value cutoff to use for the\nsearch. If no value is provided, a default evalue of 1e-20 will be used.\n\nThe caller may specify what columns should be included in the output.\nBy default, the included columns are\n\n    sseqid\n    pident\n    length\n    mismatcch\n    gapopen\n    qstart\n    qend\n    sstart\n    send\n    evalue\n    bitscore\n\nExplanations of these columns may be found at\nhttps://www.metagenomics.wiki/tools/blast/blastn-output-format-6\n\nIf the caller desires to include additional columns, it may provide\nthem to the additional_columns parameter.\n\nParameters:\n    subject:            Path(s) to subject sequence FASTA file(s).\n    query:              Path to query sequence FASTA file.\n    evalue (float):     Expect value cutoff to use in BLAST search.\n    out_columns:        Output columns to include in results.\n    additional_columns: Additional output columns to include in results.\n    db_cache:           BlastDBCache that tells where to find BLAST DBs.\n    threads (int):      Number of threads to use for BLAST search.\n    dust (bool):        Filter low-complexity regions from search.\n    task (str):         Parameter preset to use.\n    max_targets (int):  Maximum number of target seqs to include.\n    n_seqidlist (str):  Specifies seqids to ignore.\n    debug (bool):       Whether to enable debug features."]}, {"name": "simple_blast.blasting.BlastnSearch.query", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Return the query sequence path."]}, {"name": "simple_blast.blasting.BlastnSearch.subject", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Iterable", "xref": {"fqname": "collections.abc.Iterable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Return the subject sequence paths."]}, {"name": "simple_blast.blasting.BlastnSearch.seq1_path", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Return the subject sequence paths."]}, {"name": "simple_blast.blasting.BlastnSearch.seq2_path", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Return the query sequence path."]}, {"name": "simple_blast.blasting.BlastnSearch.evalue", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Return the expect value used as a cutoff in the blastn search."]}, {"name": "simple_blast.blasting.BlastnSearch.db_cache", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "BlastDBCache", "xref": {"fqname": "simple_blast.blasting.blastdb_cache.BlastDBCache", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Return a cache of BLAST DBs to be used in the search."]}, {"name": "simple_blast.blasting.BlastnSearch.hits", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "pd.DataFrame", "xref": {"fqname": "pandas.DataFrame", "project": "pandas"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Return a dataframe containing this search's BLAST results."]}, {"name": "simple_blast.blasting.BlastnSearch.threads", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Return the number of threads to use for the search."]}, {"name": "simple_blast.blasting.BlastnSearch.dust", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Return whether to filter low-complexity regions."]}, {"name": "simple_blast.blasting.BlastnSearch.task", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Return the name of the parameter preset to use."]}, {"name": "simple_blast.blasting.BlastnSearch.max_targets", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Return the maximum number of target sequences."]}, {"name": "simple_blast.blasting.BlastnSearch.negative_seqidlist", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Return a path to a list of sequence IDs to ignore."]}, {"name": "simple_blast.blasting.BlastnSearch.out_columns", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Return the list of columns to include in the output."]}, {"name": "simple_blast.blasting.BlastnSearch._build_blast_command", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "simple_blast.blasting.BlastnSearch._get_hits", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A search (alignment) to be made with blastn.\n\nThis class provides a programmer-friendly way to define the parameters of a\nsimple blastn search, carry out the search, and parse the results.\n\nThe most useful property of a BlastnSearch instance is hits. hits runs the\ndefined blastn search (if it hasn't been run already), parses the results,\nstores them in a pandas dataframe, and returns the result.\n\nValues passed to the constructor may be retrieved through the class's\nproperties.\n\nAttributes:\n    debug (bool): Whether to enable debug features for this instance."]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "simple_blast.blastdb_cache", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "simple_blast.blastdb_cache.read_js_title", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "js", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["def read_nal_title(nal):", "with open(nal, \"r\") as nal_file:", "for l in nal_file:", "if not l.startswith(\"#\"):", "split = l.rstrip().split(\" \")", "if split[0] == \"TITLE\":", "return frozenset(", "map(", "Path,", "split[1:]", ")", ")"]}, {"name": "simple_blast.blastdb_cache.read_nin_title", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "nin", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "simple_blast.blastdb_cache.get_existing", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "location", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "simple_blast.blastdb_cache.to_path_iterable", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "ix", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "Iterable", "xref": {"fqname": "collections.abc.Iterable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "simple_blast.blastdb_cache.convert_index", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "f", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "self_i", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "paths_i", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "simple_blast.blastdb_cache.title_parsers", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "simple_blast.blastdb_cache.BlastDBCache", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "simple_blast.blastdb_cache.BlastDBCache.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "location", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "find_existing", "type": null, "default": "..